<dl id="s18006d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="us18" href="#s18006d">Penelope: </a><a href="../../FF/unbs/s18all.htm#s18006d">sector 6(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> games high tomb on peaks</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[When all was consumed save the white bones, Achilles&apos; remains were placed in a pot along with the bones of Patroclus, but not with the dust of Antilochus, and the urn was buried under a great tomb &lsquo;high on the jutting headland over wide Hellespont&rsquo; that it might be seen from the grey sea by sailors then and thereafter and marvelled at. <br> The mother of Achilles asks for funereal games to be held with glorious prizes, gifts of the gods, even of Thetis, the silver-footed.]</font> <small> Butcher &amp; Lang, trans. <a name="OHBL4" href="/udra/udex.htm#OHBL4"><cite title="source">The Odyssey Of Homer</cite></a> (1906), p. 390</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
